value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of meiosis I, a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the first phase of meiosis, in which cells divide and homologous chromosomes are paired and segregated from each other, producing two daughter cells.

A part of a cellular organism that is either an immaterial entity or a material entity with granularity above the level of a protein complex but below that of an anatomical system. Or, a substance produced by a cellular organism with granularity above the level of a protein complex.

label.value: DNA synthesis involved in mitochondrial DNA replication

value.value: Any DNA biosynthetic process that is involved in mitochondrial DNA replication.
A prolongation or process extending from a cell and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of plasma membrane bounded cell projections.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a plasma membrane bounded prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a cilium or axon.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of a plasma membrane bounded cell projection are generated and organized.
All of the contents of a plasma membrane bounded neuron projection, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the projection.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the deposition or modulates the distribution of coloring matter in an organism.
One of the two nuclear divisions that occur as part of the meiotic cell cycle.

A mitotic cell cycle process comprising the steps by which the nucleus of a eukaryotic cell divides; the process involves condensation of chromosomal DNA into a highly compacted form. Canonically, mitosis produces two daughter nuclei whose chromosome complement is identical to that of the mother cell.
The cellular processes that contribute to exocytosis.

label.value: cell-cell adhesion in response to extracellular stimulus

value.value: The attachment of one cell to another cell via adhesion molecules as a result of an extracellular stimulus.

The process in which a mitochondrial gene's sequence is converted into a mature gene product or products (proteins or RNA). This includes the production of an RNA transcript as well as any processing to produce a mature RNA product or an mRNA or circRNA (for protein-coding genes) and the translation of that mRNA or circRNA into protein. Protein maturation is included when required to form an active form of a product from an inactive precursor form.
Translation that occurs at the presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: translation at presynapse, modulating chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: Translation that occurs at the presynapse, and that modulates chemical synaptic transmission.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: A vesicle-mediated transport process in which the presynapse take up external materials or membrane constituents by the invagination of a small region of the plasma membrane to form a new membrane-bounded vesicle.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Translation that occurs at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Any process that regulates translation occurring at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Any process that regulates translation occurring at the presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: A cellular process in which two or more cells combine together, their plasma membrane fusing, producing a single cell. In some cases, nuclei fuse, producing a polyploid cell, while in other cases, nuclei remain separate, producing a syncytium.
The directed movement of some substance from a cell, into the extracellular region. This may occur via transport across the plasma membrane or via exocytosis.

label.value: negative regulation of mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint signaling

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of negative regulation of mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint signaling.

A stable assembly of two or more macromolecules, i.e. proteins, nucleic acids, carbohydrates or lipids, in which at least one component is a protein and the constituent parts function together in the nucleus.
A protein complex that is part of an endoplasmic reticulum.
Reactions triggered in response to the presence of a symbiont that act to protect or prevent damage to the host.
The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a non-membrane-bounded organelle.

label.value: disruption of cellular anatomical structure in another organism

value.value: The disruption of a cellular component of another organism, leading to damage or temporary subversion of that structure. In some cases this can cause malfunctioning of the cells and death of the target organism.

label.value: disruption of anatomical structure in another organism

value.value: The disruption of an anatomical structure of another organism, leading to damage or temporary subversion of that structure.

An intracellular signaling module that is part of larger signaling pathways that can be initiated either intracellularly or by cell surface receptors. Intracellular signaling cassettes are discrete signaling units that are often shared by multiple signaling pathways.
The biosynthetic process resulting in the formation of a nucleic acid.

definition.value: This term should not be used for direct annotation. It should be possible to make a more specific annotation to one of the children of this term.

value.value: The cellular DNA metabolic process resulting in the breakdown of a nucleic acid.

definition.value: This term should not be used for direct annotation. It should be possible to make a more specific annotation to one of the children of this term.

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of dendrite development.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of peroxisome organization.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of peroxisome organization.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuromuscular synaptic transmission.

label.value: negative regulation of neuromuscular synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neuromuscular synaptic transmission.

label.value: positive regulation of neuromuscular synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neuromuscular synaptic transmission.

label.value: positive regulation of G1/S transition of mitotic cell cycle

value.value: Any signaling pathway that increases or activates a cell cycle cyclin-dependent protein kinase to modulate the switch from G1 phase to S phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: regulation of endoplasmic reticulum unfolded protein response

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of endoplasmic reticulum unfolded protein response.

label.value: negative regulation of endoplasmic reticulum unfolded protein response

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of endoplasmic reticulum unfolded protein response.

label.value: positive regulation of endoplasmic reticulum unfolded protein response

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of endoplasmic reticulum unfolded protein response.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a protein or other molecule binding to a receptor.
Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a protein or other molecule binding to a receptor.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a protein or other molecule binding to a receptor.

label.value: regulation of protein localization to nucleus

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to nucleus.

label.value: negative regulation of protein localization to nucleus

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to nucleus.

label.value: positive regulation of protein localization to nucleus

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to nucleus.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of oocyte maturation.
Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of oocyte maturation.
